text: Dominique Tian (born December 14, 1959 in Marseille) was a member of the National Assembly of France. He represented Bouches-du-Rhône's 2nd constituency from 2002 to 2017, as a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1959 births Category:Living people Category:People from Marseille Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:The Popular Right Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
